LICENSE AND ATTRIBUTION FOR ground_truth/
=========================================

This directory contains material under two different licenses. Read all
three sections before redistributing any part of it.

  Section 1  CC BY 4.0   net_gt_ui_overlays/*.png       (CGHD images)
  Section 2  MIT         *.json, wire_labels/*.txt       (our annotations)
  Section 3  CC BY 4.0   component_labels/*.txt          (CGHD annotations)


1. IMAGES — CC BY 4.0 (derived from CGHD-1152)
----------------------------------------------

Applies to: `net_gt_ui_overlays/*.png` (34 files)

These files are ADAPTATIONS of images from the CGHD-1152 dataset.

  Original work: CGHD1152 — A Public Ground-Truth Dataset for Handwritten
                 Circuit Diagram Images
  Creators:      Felix Thoma, Johannes Bayer, Yakun Li
  Affiliation:   Smart Data & Knowledge Services, DFKI GmbH,
                 Kaiserslautern, Germany
  Source:        https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6385814
  License:       Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
                 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

STATEMENT OF MODIFICATIONS (required by CC BY 4.0 §3(a)(1)(B)):

The original CGHD-1152 photographs were modified as follows, by
`wire_detection/benchmark/gen_batch.py`:

  a. converted from colour to 8-bit grayscale, then back to a 3-channel
     BGR representation;
  b. resampled to 1408x1408 pixels by bicubic interpolation (roughly a
     4x upscale);
  c. overlaid with dark polylines marking the dataset's ground-truth wire
     segments.

The underlying photograph — including paper texture, lighting gradient, and
the drafter's original pen strokes — is retained in these files. They are
adaptations, not independent works.

These 34 PNG files remain licensed CC BY 4.0. Redistributing them requires
crediting the creators above, linking the license, and indicating that
changes were made. This notice satisfies those conditions; if you
redistribute the files, carry this notice with them.

No warranty is given by the original creators. CC BY 4.0 is offered
"as-is" and disclaims warranties to the extent permitted.


2. ANNOTATIONS — MIT
--------------------

Applies to: `real_nets_verified.json`, `real_nets_working.json`,
            `real_nets_vlm9.json`, `net_gt_ui_meta.json`,
            `chris_ground_truth/*.zip`, `wire_labels/*.txt`

These are original work by the authors of this repository (see
`../LICENSE.txt`) and are released under the MIT License.

They encode electrical net membership, component identity, and
ground-truth wire polylines. They reference CGHD-1152 images by filename
only and contain no image data. Using them requires obtaining the
CGHD-1152 images separately — see `README.md` in this directory.

Although these annotations describe CGHD-1152 images, they are not
adaptations of them in the copyright sense: the human-verified net-level
connectivity ground truth was traced and confirmed independently, the
wire polylines in `wire_labels/` were drawn by us, and no equivalent
annotation exists in the source dataset.

ONE CARVE-OUT. The `bboxes` field of `net_gt_ui_meta.json` holds
component bounding boxes taken from CGHD-1152's own annotations (verified:
they agree with `component_labels/` to within ~3 px at 1408x1408). Those
coordinates are covered by Section 3, not by this section. What is ours in
that file is the selection of electrically-relevant components and their
integer indexing, which `real_nets_verified.json` refers to.


3. COMPONENT ANNOTATIONS — CC BY 4.0 (derived from CGHD-1152)
--------------------------------------------------------------

Applies to: `component_labels/*.txt` (134 files, 5233 boxes)
            the `bboxes` field of `net_gt_ui_meta.json`

These are ADAPTATIONS of CGHD-1152's own component annotations — not
independent work. Same creators, source, and license as Section 1:

  Creators:  Felix Thoma, Johannes Bayer, Yakun Li
  Source:    https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6385814
  License:   CC BY 4.0  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

STATEMENT OF MODIFICATIONS (required by CC BY 4.0 §3(a)(1)(B)):

  a. exported through Roboflow to YOLO oriented-bounding-box format: one
     line per component, `<class> x1 y1 x2 y2 x3 y3 x4 y4`, corner
     coordinates normalised to [0,1] against the image's width and height;
  b. classes re-indexed to the 58-entry list in the export's `data.yaml`
     (mirrored by `COMPONENT_TYPES` in `wire_detection/benchmark/`);
  c. coordinates re-quantised to float — reproducible only to ~1 px;
  d. restricted to the 134 images of the wire-detection benchmark.

Roboflow emits several `.rf.<hash>` copies per image, most of them
geometrically augmented. Only the copy pixel-identical to the original
CGHD photograph is reproduced here; `component_labels/identity_manifest.json`
records which one, per image. No CGHD image data is included.

Redistributing these files requires crediting the creators above, linking
the license, and indicating that changes were made. This notice satisfies
those conditions; carry it with the files.


4. IF YOU USE THIS BENCHMARK
----------------------------

Cite both the source dataset and this work:

  F. Thoma, J. Bayer, Y. Li, and A. Dengel, "A public ground-truth dataset
  for handwritten circuit diagram images," in Proc. Int. Conf. Document
  Analysis and Recognition (ICDAR), 2021, pp. 20-27.
  Dataset: https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6385814

  See `../CITATION.cff` for the citation of this repository and its paper.
